I visited this establishment for the very first time on Saturday and I live in Queens, NY. I saw a review on "Good Eats" with Lauren Glassberg and wanted to give it a try to support but to my dismay I was not impressed with the overall service. I ordered the chicken and biscuit which was tasty(but way too much bread for me) and kale patties which I never got to taste after waiting nearly 1 hour.  The store opened at 1pm and I got there at 1:10pm, they had no change if you were paying cash and the young guy taking orders said the patties were in the oven and would be ready in 10 min. I shopped around the area, came back after 30 minutes still no text that my order was ready, after inquiring 50 minutes later he said he didnt know why the patties were not ready and didnt know how long it would be...really? I asked him to refund my money for everything and he said the chicken and biscuit was ready(sitting in the bag). I asked him why was the wait so long and he said they were having a bike event and preparing food and drinks for them. I heard enough, what type of business practice is that? a customer is a customer. If you cannot keep up with the volume and know in advance you are catering a event then close the establishment for the day. It isnt fair to keep customers ordering on site waiting for 1 hour for an order while you serve other customers in a park immediately. There was another gentleman waiting for so long and he also asked for a refund and left without his order. I  left there very disappointed and no desire to go back, first impressions are lasting. The food may be awesome but the service was lousy.

I came from the northernmost tip of Manhattan (Inwood) to try Sol Sips as I had seen so much buzz about it online but knew no one who had actually eaten there. If you're taking a long trip, just know that seating is limited, it's crowded in there and that there are no bathrooms for customers so be prepared. The seating was only for nine, on stools inside and for two on a little cafe table outside. Since there was no order to the seating, it was every man/woman for themselves to grab a seat whether it's their turn or not and tolerate crumbs or oil on the tables. People who came in after me managed to get themselves seated while I was waiting on line. I waited my turn only to find out that people would come in behind me and take seats or have friends hold one down while the other party arrived. Very frustrating and confusing. I managed to get a bench seat at  a bench near the window and put a bag there while I placed my order. I sipped on a little juice while my food was being made, keeping the bathroom situation in mind (long ride there and back). My order wasn't at all like what I saw in a YouTube video. I did enjoy the oyster mushrooms and my drink but the waffles were dry and they didn't offer a topping. I asked for syrup but they only had agave---which wasn't tasty. I had to ask for a fork and knife. I only got a fork so I asked again. I never finished the waffles. A couple who wanted to sit together asked me to move from where I was on the bench so that they could eat together and try each other's food. I know I saw the woman earlier at a table to herself in the back so I wondered why she had moved to the bench until her party arrived. The whole Musical Chairs seating situation is frustrating and confusing. It should be regulated, somehow. I asked the owner, who was very friendly about what I saw in the video and she expressed that the biscuits were put on a waffle press the video. I therefore bought another meal to go so I could try what I saw but it made my experience there pricey. I wanted to give the food another try at home in more calm, comfortable surroundings. The vegan (oyster mushroom)  chicken and biscuits (pressed into two mini waffles) were indeed delicious with the innovative additions of avocado and raspberry jam. They do vegan chick'n right! The turmeric biscuits were a nice touch. I had a kale salad as separate side---it was okay. I would bring vegan friends as our favorite places in Manhattan closed down. We must prepare for a long ride of two trains, another long wait for food and cross our fingers for a seat. After all of that, there are no customer bathrooms.  We can just cover the tables with napkins if there is no wipe-down. That said, the stars are for the food and the mission. I still think it's important to support this business as they grow.  I'm sure they will.

I am no vegan, and if you're reading this you probably aren't too. This review can be for both kinds of people though.  I ordered the "lobster" mac and cheese, while my mother ordered the "chicken" sandwich; we also got a smoothie, a cookie, home fries, and a side of avocado.  Starting with the main meals, I had to say overall that they were good. The mac and cheese was, well, cheesy, but with an overpowering seaweed flavor that they add with a poor addition of kale (I hate kale, but that's just me). The sandwich that I had tried was dry, lacked seasoning, and felt that the raspberry jam that comes with it doesn't mix well with the mix that comes with.  For the rest of our meal, the cookie was surprisingly good, being soft and chewy, while smoothie had a nice incorporation of flavors. The home fries were nearly over seasoned, but the ketchup or hot sauce makes a good balance (if you don't like either, they can stand good alone). The avocado was avocado, of course it was good.  For price and portion sizes, they tend to be good. All the food that we had came at a reasonable price for a reasonable portion size, and if you're a vegan it's definitely worth it. All I can really say is, do not get the avocado. $1.50 for maybe a quarter of an entire avocado is not worth it at all.  Though I have never eaten at a vegan restaurant prior, it was still very good, but as I said after eating, "it's worth money, but not my money."

As of this review I am still waiting on my primary order for a Chik'un Biscuit Sandwich and a Green Banana Tamale. I also ordered a chocolate chip cookie and a lentil patty. When I placed my initial order at 2:17pm, I was told there would be a 35 minute wait. The time is currently 3:06pm and I was told my primary order will be an additional 15 minutes. This is disappointing as I made my decision to wait for the order based on the 35 minute wait time. 1hr 15minutes is unacceptable if I was not given the opportunity to determine if I was capable of waiting this long when my order was placed.  As per what I've eaten so far, the chocolate chip cookie was delicious - I give it a 5/5 and the lentil patty left some to be desired, so I give it a 3/5. When I finally receive my food I will either update this review or post a secondary one.  The staff is cordial. The kitchen is small and the demand is high, so understandably the food would take time to prepare. People are excited to support a vegan restaurant run by a young black woman. Me especially. My advice to the restaurant for future success is to under promise and over deliver. If you think an order will take 45 minutes, tell your customers it will be an hour to an hour 15. This way they can manage their time accordingly and not feel enslaved to waiting for a meal that should have arrived 25 minutes prior.  UPDATE: Around 3:20pm, my order still was not ready. I had to leave as I was supposed to have left by 3pm at the latest. One of the staff members (I'm assuming the manager) offered to comp my entire meal and give me a full refund when I informed them that I had to leave and could not wait any longer. I appreciated the gesture but did not want my meal comped because I wanted to support their business. While the staff member was assisting with the refund, another employee informed me the chik'un biscuit sandwich was ready, so I had that and the manager refunded my other order (green banana tamale). She also gave me a voucher for a comped meal on a following visit, which I appreciated. Because of the attempt to rectify the situation, I raised my rating from 3 stars to 4. The chik'un biscuit sandwich was very good. I give it a 4/5 because it could have used more jam and maybe another sauce, but the oyster mushroom "chicken" was phenomenal.  I likely will not come back on a weekend because the wait was overwhelming but the food was good. My advice to the staff and owners is to stay calm and kind under pressure. It is understood that you are overwhelmed with work because of high volume combined with a small kitchen but that is because business is good and the food is also, so that is a blessing! Look into ways to streamline your prep time and make high volume periods go by more easily. Take inventory of peak hours and biggest sellers and do as much advance prep and pre cooking as possible to ease tension in your kitchen until you move to a bigger space where you can hire more staff. Most importantly, under promise and over deliver. Worldwide Tacos in Los Angeles has a very small kitchen with insanely long wait times, but they are up front with their customers about wait times and overestimate instead of underestimating time necessary for food prep based on volume. Some customers may not be able to wait but some will and all will appreciate that their time was not taken for granted. We live in an era of speed, efficiency and schedules. People always have places to be. So make sure you are mindful of this. Overestimate your wait times and take phone numbers go call clients. You don't want the quality of your food and your service to be overshadowed by underestimated wait times.

Genuinely confused why pancakes took an hour as my boyfriend ordered separate and that was all he ordered. I'm genuinely disappointed because I was very excited to try this black woman owned vegan restaurant, but it just took way too long. I hope they improve their kitchen flow in the future so that more people will enjoy the experience.

1. Waited over hour for my food., 2. Some people ordered after me got food and left. 3. Chicken biscuit sandwich(biscuit tasted raw) mac and cheese was 3/5 stars. Ordered 2 different shakes but they tasted the same. Shakes I rated 2/5 something tasted spoil in shake. Home fries was 4/5 stars.  The sweet potato cheese cake was great 5/5 stars, the Avocado order was great.

The wait time was entirely too long. Took over an hour and a half just to receive the food and it wasn’t up to par. I ordered the chic and waffle sandwich, lobster Mac n cheese, home fries, and two smoothies. (I was hungry) All of which lacked seasoning. The smithies were bitter. They indeed have GREAT customer service and kept a positive attitude.
Quaint, delish vegan bites and truly fulling portions!
The food was amazing, I had the chickn biscuit and sweet potato cake. service was good. Very cozy place. The wait was worth it and will definitely be going back again.

Giving it 3 stars because I’m still willing to come back and give them another shot. Overall, customer service was great. Being it was a small space with a small kitchen the wait time was 30mins. But suddenly it was an additional 20mins, with a total of 50mins.. our commute back is 50mins to and from. As a young woman from the same industry, I reeeeealllly want to give her 5 stars, but the main reason im giving 3 was due to the fact the sandwhich I ordered wasn’t as phenomenal as I thought it would be. I can taste the care and thought into the Tamarind Jackfruit panini, however it was such a let down that the bread was actually a tortilla than a flat bread. Overall, the panini was monotoned and overpoweringly sweet. I love sweet BBQ dishes but the kale and bread was not substantial enough for the flavor and mount of tamarind jackfruit. I constantly found myself needing to wash of the sugary palate after a couple bites. Honestly. Would be great with something Smokey, like bell peppers to balance out the flavor. Maybe next time I’ll try out their other dishes... sending growth and prosperity to the young owner.
Good veggie food 😋

Heard about this place and the story of a young woman opening her own place at such a young age. I wanted to go and show my support over the weekend. The variety of the food was good, shows a great diversity that vegan food can have. However, like I saw on a lot of other reviews the wait was just unnecessary long...I went with a friend and I waited an hour for my omelette, Mac and cheese and a juice and my friend waited over an hour for a latte and the pancakes. Makes the whole experience really not that pleasing when I personally paid 32 dollars to wait so long. The more frustrating thing was we saw people that came in AFTER us get their food first. Luckily we weren’t in a rush but if this place is going to last the organization of orders really needs to be worked on.
One smoothie and two gluten free pancakes. We waited for an hour and ended up leaving without our food because we had to catch our flight... Very disappointing to not warn us about the wait

The only reason I am giving a one star review is because i didnt even get to eat a meal. When I called to make a reservation, they told me I shouldnt come on a Sunday because the wait would be too long, as sunday is their busy day. On the phone the guy didnt answer with a “hello this is sol sips”, he just said “hi?”. I asked to make a reservation being that we are from long island and wanted to secure a spot before driving an hour and a half to go eat (based on their reviews, I figured I should make a reservation because there is a clear lack of control regarding their efficiency). I understand it is a small place, and its hard to control the volume with their increasing popularity....but maybe at least try NOT to turn costumers away. Maybe instead try “Sunday is a really busy day so you will have to expect a long wait, or you can try coming on a week day” something a bit more personal. Answering and NOT even introducing your business, halfway listening to me speak, and then saying youre better off not coming today.... doesnt seem like a great start. I was making a trip into brooklyn specifically and only to get food here, but i guess its a no go for me.

Horrible experience. I waited 45 minutes in a small space for a “stuffed plantain”, which really was one single plantain cut into 3 pieces and drowned in a can of beans and peppers. The taste didn’t even make up for it. I also ordered an avocado mushroom panini melt and all I got was bland mushrooms covered in black pepper with bits of avocado and soggy tomatoes and bread. Definitely not a panini, more of a wrap. Wasted $32 and STILL ended up having to buy a meal somewhere else to make up for it 🤦🏼‍♀️ NOT WORTH THE HYPE, NOT WORTH IT AT ALL. Don’t waste your time and money.
Took 45 minutes to make but it’s so good.
They take like 50 mins to an hour to make one thing. Why say it’s guna be 20 mins if it’s actually going to be an hour and they know it will be. Good food but wait times are absolutely terrible.

Delicious Jackfruit panini sandwich! It is messy to eat, so that's my only knock on the dish. But it tastes really good. Add a few drops of their hot sauce for a nice added kick of heat.  There wasn't a long wait time during my experience; really nice, warm service.  My only knock is how it isn't the best spot for dining-in since it's a small space with an open kitchen.  It can get a bit smoky in there and it irritated my eyes, so I'd recommend picking up rather than eating in. Aside from that, support a black business while enjoying great food!

I have heard about this place from tasty and was very excited to visit this tiny cosy vegan place in Bushwick.. the wait time was a little too long but the food was so delicious - the vegan Mac cheese was delightful and is a must try - I loved it so much.  It was a great experience and I loved the vibe of this cosy place. Will go back for more..

The wait time was way too long. It 45 mins for them to deliver two dishes (one dish was just a sandwich). The jerk jack fruit dish was also inedible. There was no seasoning on the two sides that come with the jerk fruit dish. The only seasoning was on the jerk jack fruit itself and all it was was way too much pepper and nothing else. It had no jerk flavor what so ever. The cook added so much pepper to the dish that while cooking it, the pepper smell became so strong that people started coughing in the place and the door had to be propped open which made it get cold in the establishment very fast. When the lack of seasoning was mentioned to the cook, she laughed and said we definitely season are food, & then said that the jerk jack fruit flavors were suppose to taste like that and suggested that I wasn’t use to jerk flavoring (mind you I’m West Indian and was raised on jerk flavors). I wanted this place to be a success & support it especially with it being a black owned vegan establishment. I strongly believe in supporting black owned establishments (especially ones championing health) but honestly after that experience i can’t see myself going back. Hope they can change for the better, because I still want to see them win.
Excellent food 👍 🔥🔥 hot sauce!!

Ugh where do I begin... We went there on Saturday morning and little that we knew that we would have to wait for an hour for 2 mediocre sandwiches, that were bottom line dry and unimpressive. There was just the girl at the cashier and one guy cooking. They clearly are not set up to handle 3 - 4 orders at a time... The place is very tiny, I understand but still. Why the hell do you take a bunch of orders if you can’t  produce? Not cool. Would never go back or recommend this place to anyone.
#blackgirlmagic personified thru vegan cuisine. Francesca Chaney and her creations and simply inspirational. That Jerk Jackfruit is amazing.
The Best made to order Vegan Spot in Brooklyn. The Food is always fresh and the staff is so welcoming.
Great vegan food! ...But not fast be prepared for a bit of wait.
Great healthy food!
Very good food! Friendly staff with good service. Everything is made fresh to order.

(Translated by Google) The girls are very nice! The food was extremely good. I'm not really a fan of vegan food but that was something new!  (Original) Die Mädels sind mega lieb! Das essen war extrem gut. Ich bin eigentlich kein fan von veganem food aber das war mal was neues!

Excellent vegan food! The wait was long but the food is great. Cheesy garlic sticks esp good.
Great atmosphere. Great food and beverages. Wonderful friendly staff.
Great flavor and it is a warm and cozy cafe. Will be back.
Awesome food and excellent customer service!

The food was quite tasty. I had the breakfast burrito, the green banana with okra and the kale salad and would each one again. Portion sizes were good and everything was flavorful, well seasoned. This place is a great option to have in the area.
The bacon, egg, and cheese with the burdock brew was everything 😍!!! I can’t wait to go back. The owner and all of the staff are also extremely sweet.
Phenomenal!

I wanted to love this place but the wait for our food was close to two hours. It left a very sour taste. We ordered chips and hummus which were bottom of the bag chips, barely enough to go with the hummus. My daughter had an “egg” sandwich and I had the breakfast burrito. The food was good but the wait was something I’ve never encountered and we never will eat there again. My daughter got her shake and I got mine a half hour later. The two couples that came in after us got half of their food before us. As much as I want to support a vegan small business I can assure you -   NEVER AGAIN.
Nice spot for takeout. Not  much room for dining in. Food was great

I’m not vegan; but I didn’t even realize my orders didn’t have meat in them. I bought the Tamarind jackfruit panini, cheesy garlic sticks, and the bacon kale tomato (bkt) flatbread. Ohh yeah, can’t forget about the chocolate chips and oatmeal cookies. Next time I would like to try the lentil patty. I had the riverside drink and that was just as flavorful. This place is a must go.
Great food and service. Definitely recommend ..
Love it!
Food and service was excellent. The wait time needs some improvement but I will be lenient because I want to the business to succeed. I love this place.

I visit Sol Sips today 12/17/18 for this writer the wait was well worth it the food  melts in your  mouth,  for those whose goings to patronize this eatery please realize that this ower put a personal touch on every dish that she makes, that alone is well worth wait for this healthy food, as she grows the wait time will  get better.
Incredible food, great service, and most of all, an inspiring story.
Very lovely place. The service was excellent. The food was awesome.

Decided to come by today because I saw a post on Facebook and I love to try new vegan places. Everyone was super friendly, food took a little while but I didn’t mind. I had the jackfruit  wrap. Garlic bread and cookies. Everything was so good ! I definitely will be back soon 💖
Amazing smoothies
Tasty vegan treats the service is a bit slow. Be prepared for a good wait for good food.
Great food and great people!
Food taste great. Very friendly and great customer service. I will highly recommend everyone to come try them out.
My daughter loves this place . It is helping her on her vegetarian journey
So good!!
LOVE

Nothing but great food and beautiful energy. I will be back for more.

Absolutely LOVE this place! Amazing, tasteful, alkaline vegan food at reasonable costs offered to the community??!!! (I recommend the "bacon, egg & cheese" & the Buddha Blu smoothie). GREAT service & just positive vibes as soon as you walk in the spot! What's not to love?!

I’ve been to so many vegan restaurants over the years. All over NYC. this has to be THE BESSSTTTT VEGAN FOOD EVERRRR. My partner and I ordered a ton and everything was just SPOT ON SPOINT. Francesca is so professional! Her customer service skills are really admirable. Definitely will be back. Worth the wait, worth the money, worth the distance.
The food was good. I recommend it!

Truly excellent vegan food. I had the mushroom avocado melt, and every bite was incredible. I also had the Blu Buddha smoothie, which was also delicious. Be sure to remember to grab some of the house-made hot sauce. They have a chipotle and jalapeno option, both are freaking fantastic.  Final point: you won't find friendlier, more helpful, more wonderful people anywhere than those that own and run this place. The positive energy is as healthy and refreshing as the food.  (It's true that you it's not the fastest, but I only waited 15 or so minutes around the lunch rush. And I'm willing to forgive a little inefficiency given the overall positive experience.)

My daughter lives in Brooklyn and she enjoys the food and supporting a young entrepreneur. We had the BKT and I had the avocado shroom melt and the food was amazing! The owner is doing a great job but you must be prepared to wait. We ordered our food before we headed there on our 15 minute walk. We still waited another 45 minutes but again, the food was really good.
Food was very tasty but the wait was a bit longer than expected. Not much space to dine in, so I suggest ordering your food to go and picking up. Excellent drinks!
So yummy and so friendly

The food is great. The atomsphere is great. The customer service is great. Everything about Sol Sips is great. Everyone should come and eat by Sol Sips!
I’ve been looking forward to trying Sol Sips since reading about the opening in Elle mag. My boyfriend and I had the chips and dip and mushroom melt. Both were great and we can’t wait to come back!!

Went there on a weekend for brunch.  We waited over 2 hours for our order, we had to go next door to buy food to tie us over in the meantime.  After 2 hours, the orders were finally delivered one dish at a time over a period of 30 minutes and only because we kept asking.  They seemed to have no idea what the orders even were, they had to ask people what they were waiting for.  Nice food but never again, really bad experience.
Tiny spot with a tiny menu — great tasting and with good vibes!
Cute small space ,wouldn't recommend eating in if you want some elbow room. But TOGO holds up well. Props to the lady who served us. She ran the register and was the one cooking too.

My first experience was good, it was the perfect time to come in because I took my time to scope the menu which had some nice selections. I had a root brew of burdock with coconut milk which was surprisingly good because burdock has a strong, earthy taste and I’m not always a fan of coconut milk in my beverages. I had the BKT sandwich and honestly tempeh bacon is hit or miss, but it was really good and the vegetables were fresh. I’ll be back!
I had the best waffles here but the latte had no flavor. I will be going back to try some of the other dishes. I was also impressed with the very young owner.
The avocado mushroom melt was so good.
Amazing!

I've had their cacao drink twice now, once iced and once hot, and it's very good. Will be back for more. Had friendly chats with the staff each time, and one person (the owner?) remembered me even after I visited only once. Rooting for this small business to make it big!

I met the owner of the establishment who was very pleasant and welcoming. I enjoyed the jackfruit pannini,  cinnamon glazed donut and strawberry lavender lemonade. The wait time for my food was less than 10 minutes.

Sol Sips is a delicious neighborhood vegan joint! The owner is usually there and she’s pleasant too. The food is really really good and my personal favorite is the BKT and Jackfruit Panini. The service is pretty good, but the wait times are always disappointing. It is a small business, but you’re almost always going to wait over 30 minutes for your order... So, if you have time to kill or you’re getting something like a donut, I’d recommend this tasty vegan joint!
Nice spot for vegan brunch
Just had the mushroom avocado melt. Off the chain! Nice and clean. Must have vegan for the bushwick area.

Good service, a little bit expensive. The menu is not extensive. I didn't lime my drink though

I heard the dude at the register making fun of me in the kitchen for pronouncing one of the juice names wrong :( The juice was super good though! The mushroom melt was tasty but the cheese wasn't nearly melted and there was so little avocado, especially considering that it was $10. I was so ready to love this place, I love the vibe and the mission, it just didn't quite deliver food wise.

I didn't eat or order any thing .they were closing i just inquiring food selection and pricing.They were helpful and well mannered.
This place is the best kept secret in New York. The food is excellent and it's very cozy. Also the staff is very friendly. I highly recommend it!

Overall Sol Sips is a quaint spot with outstanding service. I was disappointed with the portion size and the overall taste of the item I ordered which was avocado mushroom melt. It was cold and contained very little avocado,  I wish the cheese was melted so that dish was warm.

Francesca and her staff are beautiful people who are clearly doing something they love. The menu is not carved in stone, and you can make changes to any item to accommodate personal needs. E everything we had was excellent, and I was allowed to modify my smoothie to my taste. I highly recommend Sol Sips!

I can't say enough great things about All, her mom, and the team she's assembling. I go there as work all day someone's as a colorful cast of characters pass thru.  there have been lively discussions and great conversations. ... and, the best food! If you love mushrooms, get the avocado mushroom melt, also the jackfruit panini is a must. All of the juices and smoothies are a must.  the hummus and chips... there are so many exceptional others.  breakfast burritos... There are also vegan doughnuts ... always offered with exceptional service and  great conversation. Sol will remember your name and your story. If you go once you're family.
Tasty food, kind service, great vibes. They have a house baker so their rolls and such are extra fancy and extra fresh. I will certainly be back.

Love love this place. The set up is so nice, Francesha and her mother are lovely people ! I had the avocado melt soooooo good. YES theres a wait but the wait is worth it so please, if you’re in a rush dont bother.
Jack fruit was great , light sandwich and flavorful.
Best place ever!!!! Great service, great food, great vibes & great family. What more can you ask for?! I hope they get a bigger spot soon because I predict things will be picking up for them. :)

Great spot for healthy drinks and treats. So far I’ve tried the Jackfruit panini, burdock root coffee on one to go visit uand then the dandelion coffee, “sea” bowl, and banana muffin on another. Prices are decent for the quality of the food. My only issue was when, during my second visit, I found my “ sea” bowl to not have any quinoa, which basically would of made this more enjoyable. Nonetheless I am happy to frequent this cozy vegan spot.
Great atmosphere and great customer service with plenty of healthy options on the menu
Great!

Amazing initiative, however the wait (on a Saturday afternoon) was insane for our food, they forgot a part of my order, and then took 15 minutes to make one smoothie. Just overall very disorganized in a very tight space which I’m sure made it worse.

Delicious food and warm service. Such a rarity in New York. All vegan! I had the waffles for my brunch and they were scrumptious.

The owner and her mom sooo sweet. Felt like I was at home. The aeustetic is so nice and the food is AMAZING 😋 I got a bacon egg and cheese and my boyfriend ordered the jackfruit panini both was delicious. Definitely going back soon!

I visited this place on a Saturday afternoon, it was crowded. I ordered three blueberry pancakes, an avocado and mushroom omelette and two lattes. As soon as I cut into the pancakes the batter came running out, the omelette was cold BUT, the mushrooms were well seasoned, and the coffee was extremely watered down. On top of that I waited for two hours to receive my food, and about an hour to receive my coffee. I’m proud of this young lady for opening her own restaurant, and the staff was so nice. I was disappointed, I hope they can get it together.
